"Armd with two pointed darts,he leaves his friends; And true Achates on his steps attends. Lo ! in the deep recesses of the wood, Before his eyes his goddess mother stood— A huntress in her habit and her mien : Her dress a maid, her air confess'd a queen. Bare were her knees,and knots her garments bind ; l Loose was her hair, and wanton’d in the wind ; Herhandsustain'da bow ; her quiver hung behind. s She seenv’d a virgin of the Spartan blood : With such array Harpalyce bestrode Her Thracian courser, and out-stripp’d the rapid flood. ‘Ho! strangers! have you lately seen (she said) ( One of my sisters, like myself array'd, Who cross'd the lawn, or in the forest stray’d ? s A painted quiver at her back she bore ; ; Varied with spots, a lynx’s hide she wore ; And at full cry pursued the tusky boar.” f Thus Venus : thus her son replied again : ¢ None of your sisters have we heard or seen, O virgin ! or what other name you bear Above that style—O more than mortal fair ! Your voice and mien celestial birth betray ! If, as you seem, the sister of the day, Or one at least of chaste Diana’s train, Let not an humble suppliant sue in vain ; But tell a stranger, long in tempests toss'd, What earth we tread, and who commands the coast ? Then on your name shall wretched mortals eall, And offerd victims at your altars fall,— # I dare not, (she replied) assume the name Of goddess, or celestial honours claim :"